from deliberate Stairs use step
{Example} @version: 1
deliberate SummarizeSupportTicket when >>> run when the user provides a raw support ticket and asks for a short summary. <<<:

    mandate:
    >>> Takes a raw support ticket, cleans and normalizes its text, extracts key signals (language, entities, salient points),
    and produces two outputs: (1) a short internal summary with an issue label and a few key bullets, and (2) a concise,
    polite reply message for the user based on those points. <<<
    __mandate


    editable->frozen plan:

        in:
            raw_ticket (required) >> raw support ticket text provided by the user <<
        __in
        out:
            internal_summary >> short internal summary with issue label and key bullets <<
            user_reply >> concise, polite reply message for the user <<
        __out

        body:
            do action preprocess_ticket using [ [raw_ticket] = [raw_ticket] ] producing [ [structured_ticket] ]
            do action generate_reply using [ [structured_ticket] = [structured_ticket] ] producing [ [internal_summary], [user_reply] ]
            return [ [internal_summary], [user_reply] ]
        __body

    __
__deliberate




{Prep} @intent.goal: "Clean and normalize ticket text; extract language, entities, and salient points into a structured form."
 action preprocess_ticket >> clean the ticket text and extract key signals for downstream steps. <<:
    in:
        raw_ticket (required) >> raw support ticket text, may contain noise and formatting <<
    __in
    out:
        structured_ticket >> structured representation: normalized text, language, entities, salient points <<
    __out

    body:
        [ [text_raw] = [raw_ticket] ?? "" ]
        [ [clean_text >>normalized ticket text; trim, collapse whitespace; remove boilerplate; preserve important IDs/URLs/emails<<] = [text_raw] ]
        [ [language >> ISO 639-1 language code of the ticket <<] = [clean_text] ]
        [ [entities >> list of canonical entities (people, orgs, products, versions, order IDs, emails); deduplicated <<] = [clean_text] ]
        [ [points >> 3-5 salient points capturing problem, context, symptoms, attempted steps; terse phrases <<] = [clean_text] ]
        [ [structured_ticket] = ( "text": [clean_text], "language": [language], "entities": [entities], "points": [points] ) ]
        return [structured_ticket]
    __body
__action

{Gen} @intent.goal: "From the structured ticket, produce a short internal summary with an issue label and bullets, and a concise, polite user reply."
action generate_reply >>> generate a concise reply draft and a short internal summary from the structured ticket. <<<:
    in:
        structured_ticket (required) >> output of preprocess_ticket <<
    __in
    out:
        internal_summary >> 'label: <issue>' on first line + 3-5 bullet points <<
        user_reply >> concise, polite reply (2-4 sentences), no internal details <<
    __out

    body:
        [ [issue_label >> short issue label (2-4 words) based on points and entities; no PII; lowercase with hyphens <<] = [structured_ticket] ]
        [ [internal_summary >> short internal summary; first line 'label: ' + issue_label; then 3-5 bullets with key facts <<] = [structured_ticket] ]
        [ [user_reply >> concise, polite reply addressing user's issue; acknowledge, summarize next steps or workaround; ask for missing info if needed; 2-4 sentences; avoid internal notes <<] = [structured_ticket] ]
        return [ [internal_summary], [user_reply] ]
    __body
__action

